{{Infobox person | name=Farshid Delshad | image =Farshid Delshad.jpg | alt = Black and white photograph of Farshid Delshad | occupation = Academic, writer, translator, researcher | birth_date = <!-- Please cite a reliable source for date of birth --> | birth_place = <!-- Please cite a reliable source for place of birth --> }} '''Farshid Delshad''' ([[Persian language|Persian]]: [[فرشید دلشاد]] ) is an affiliated researcher and scholar of linguistic and [[Iranian Studies]]. He was Lecturer of Persian and Comparative Linguistics at [[University of Freiburg]] <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orient.uni-freiburg.de/islamwissenschaft/mitarbeiter/delshad |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-07-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730021148/http://www.orient.uni-freiburg.de/islamwissenschaft/mitarbeiter/delshad |archivedate=2015-07-30 |df= }}</ref> and at [[University of Bern]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zuercher-lehrhaus.ch/cms/front_content.php?idcat=166&idart=569 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-11-13 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117014955/http://www.zuercher-lehrhaus.ch/cms/front_content.php?idcat=166&idart=569 |archivedate=2015-11-17 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://linguistlist.org/people/personal/get-personal-page2.cfm?PersonID=189468 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-11-13 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902162907/http://linguistlist.org/people/personal/get-personal-page2.cfm?PersonID=189468 |archivedate=2014-09-02 |df= }}</ref> Delshad's first Phd and academic thesis at [[Tbilisi State University]] in 2000 dealt with Comparative Linguistics and Caucasian Studies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kartvfund.org.ge/index.php?act=page&id=33.57&lang=en|title=Fund for Kartvelian Studies|work=kartvfund.org.ge|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117031134/http://www.kartvfund.org.ge/index.php?act=page&id=33.57&lang=en|archivedate=2015-11-17|df=}}</ref>
Delshad received his post Doctoral from [[Friedrich Schiller University]] in Jena, Germany in Historical-Comparative Linguistics and his thesis was Philological Studies on Iranian and Semitic Loanwords in Classical Georgian,.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://linguistlist.org/issues/21/21-2020.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-07-18 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819191026/http://linguistlist.org/issues/21/21-2020.html |archivedate=2016-08-19 |df= }}</ref> He has further specialized in German and [[Indo-Germanic]] linguistics.<ref>http://www.db-thueringen.de/servlets/DerivateServlet/Derivate-3610/Diss.pdf</ref> Since 1994 he has worked as a scholar of [[Iranian languages|Iranian]] and [[comparative linguistics]] in Germany,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.orient.uni-freiburg.de/islamwissenschaft/mitarbeiter/delshad|title=Dr. Farshid Delshad|work=uni-freiburg.de|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730021148/http://www.orient.uni-freiburg.de/islamwissenschaft/mitarbeiter/delshad|archivedate=2015-07-30|df=}}</ref> and Switzerland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weltwoche.ch/ausgaben/2010-14/artikel-2010-14-bin-laden-in-biel.html|title=Bin Laden in Biel|work=weltwoche.ch|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117013927/http://www.weltwoche.ch/ausgaben/2010-14/artikel-2010-14-bin-laden-in-biel.html|archivedate=2015-11-17|df=}}</ref> Farshid Delshad has contributed to minority research,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juedische-allgemeine.de/article/view/id/14915|title=Interview: »Sie haben Angst« - Jüdische Allgemeine|author=Zentralrat der Juden in Deutschland K.d.ö.R.|work=juedische-allgemeine.de|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730014730/http://www.juedische-allgemeine.de/article/view/id/14915|archivedate=2015-07-30|df=}}</ref> namely religious <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.igfm.de/news-presse/news/jahresversammlung-2011/peter-amsler-darstellung-religioeser-minderheiten-in-iranischen-medien/|title=Peter Amsler: Die Darstellung religiöser Minderheiten in den iranischen Medien. Vortrag bei der 39. IGFM-Jahreshauptversammlung in Bonn am 19. März 2011|work=IGFM.de|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703181737/http://www.igfm.de/news-presse/news/jahresversammlung-2011/peter-amsler-darstellung-religioeser-minderheiten-in-iranischen-medien/|archivedate=2015-07-03|df=}}</ref> and ethnic populations in the [[Islamic World]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpb.de/apuz/31147/religioese-minderheiten-im-iran?p=all|title=Religiöse Minderheiten im Iran|author=Bundeszentrale für politische Bildung|work=bpb.de|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923221625/http://www.bpb.de/apuz/31147/religioese-minderheiten-im-iran?p=all|archivedate=2015-09-23|df=}}</ref> He has also written extensively on [[Intercultural Communication]] and [[Sufism]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unique-online.de/arabisch-kurdisch-und-georgisch-als-dolmetscher-auf-dem-forst-ein-interview/281/|title=Arabisch, Kurdisch und Georgisch Als Dolmetscher auf dem Forst – ein Interview|work=unique-online.de|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730005403/http://www.unique-online.de/arabisch-kurdisch-und-georgisch-als-dolmetscher-auf-dem-forst-ein-interview/281/|archivedate=2015-07-30|df=}}</ref> He is also a translator of Russian and Georgian literary works to Persian and vice versa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noormags.ir/view/en/creator/29080|title=فرشید دلشاد - Noor Specialized Magazined Website|work=noormags.ir}}</ref> He is the first Persian translator of [[the Knight in the Panther's Skin]], a Georgian medieval epic poem, written in the 12th century by Georgia's national poet [[Shota Rustaveli]]. He worked as a cultural advisor and certified interpreter for the [[United Nations]] in Geneva.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://blog.lingoking.com/dienstleister-des-monats/dienstleister-des-monats-herr-delshad |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-07-18 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814215353/https://blog.lingoking.com/dienstleister-des-monats/dienstleister-des-monats-herr-delshad |archivedate=2016-08-14 |df= }}</ref>
