{{Infobox journal | title = Patterns of Prejudice | cover = | discipline = [[Higher education]] | abbreviation = Patterns Prejudice | editor = Tony Kushner, Barbara Rosenbaum and Dan Stone | publisher = [[Taylor & Francis]] | country = UK | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1967-present | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=aimsScope&journalCode=rpop20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rpop20/current | link1-name = Online access | ISSN = 0031-322X | eISSN = 1461-7331 | LCCN = | OCLC = 757286608 | CODEN = | JSTOR = }}
'''Patterns of Prejudice''' is a [[Academic journal|journal]] about historical and contemporary social exclusion published by [[Taylor & Francis]].<ref>[http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=aimsScope&journalCode=rpop20 Aims and Scope], Patterns of Prejudice, 2015</ref> It is a [[double-blind]] peer-reviewed journal published five times a year devoted to intolerance. The journal was founded in 1967 to study "racial and religious prejudice" throughout the world and report on contemporary political events.<ref>{{Cite journal |last= |first= |title=Our Aims |journal=Patterns of Prejudice |volume=1 |issue=1 |date=1967|pages=3 |doi=10.1080/0031322X.1967.9968636 |ref=harv }}</ref>
